<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="315" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d315">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1750.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Johnson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 15, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 200
                            of the 26th ultimo in which you enclose the Legation’s recommendation
                            regarding the liquidation of diversions of revenue made by the Dominican
                            Government due to the extraordinary expenses incurred since July 7,
                            1915, in attempting to suppress uprisings in the Dominican Republic.</p>
                        <p>Your report has been read with much interest and its recommendations are
                            commended.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>